== Attributions ==

Sleezer was assembled by merging two upstream Lidarr plugins. It would not
exist without the original authors of those projects.

* Portions of the Deezer indexer, Deezer download client, ARL handling, and
  the `DeezNET` client library are Copyright (C) TrevTV and contributors, and
  were originally distributed as part of `Lidarr.Plugin.Deezer`.
    https://github.com/TrevTV/Lidarr.Plugin.Deezer
    https://github.com/TrevTV/DeezNET  (GPL-3.0)

* Portions of the Slskd indexer and download client, the multi-source web-
  client framework (Lucida, DABmusic, T2Tunes, Subsonic), the FFmpeg
  conversion pipeline (formerly "Codec Tinker"), Queue Cleaner, Search
  Sniper, custom metadata source framework, and Similar Artists recommender
  are Copyright (C) TypNull and contributors, and were originally distributed
  as part of `Tubifarry` under the MIT License.
    https://github.com/TypNull/Tubifarry  (MIT — relicensed under GPL-3.0 in Sleezer)

The MIT license under which Tubifarry is originally released is compatible
with GPL-3.0; the combined work is distributed under GPL-3.0 because the
bundled `DeezNET` library is GPL-3.0.


